The paper deals with the representation of graphs in 3D using polyhedra, which falls under computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses planar graphs and their duals, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of contact representations of graphs is related to graph theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions algorithms for constructing these representations, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the representation of non-planar graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and computational geometry (cs.GR).
